<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4001/19.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Archbishop <persName type="from">Nuttall</persName>
                                to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Kingston, Jamaica</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-21"><hi rend="italic">January
                                        21, 1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>We all appreciate deeply American sympathy in our distress and the prompt
                            visit of your men-of-war for our succor. Happily supply <pb facs="0675" n="563" xml:id="pg_563"/> of food available for relief committee is
                            sufficient. After meeting cost of this our next great want will be the
                            means for making small houses habitable. All our people are behaving
                            splendidly.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Archbishop Nuttall</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Chairman of Relief
                            Committee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>